## Troubleshooting

### "trivy: command not found"

Install via winget:

```powershell
winget install AquaSecurity.Trivy
```

Then restart your terminal.

### Husky hooks not running

```bash
# Reinstall hooks
pnpm exec husky

# Verify .husky/pre-commit exists and is executable
# On Windows, Git Bash handles execute permissions
```

### lint-staged not finding files

Verify that files are actually staged:

```bash
git diff --cached --name-only
```

### Trivy slow on first run

First run downloads the vulnerability database (~30MB). Subsequent runs use the cached database. Update with:

```bash
trivy fs --download-db-only .
```

### Skipping hooks in emergencies

```bash
git commit --no-verify -m "hotfix: critical production fix"
```

Only use for genuine emergencies. Document why in the commit message.
